## Type Aliases (`utils/int_types.go`)

```go
type Uint256 = uint256.Int   // full 256-bit
type Uint160 = uint256.Int   // logically ≤160 bits, same underlying type
type Uint128 = uint256.Int   // logically ≤128 bits
type Int256  = int256.Int    // signed 256-bit
type Int128  = int256.Int    // signed 128-bit (same underlying)
```

Boundary checks (`CheckToUint160`, `Uint128Max`, `Uint160Max`) are manual — Go type system does not enforce bit widths.

